#### Summary

RxJava exposes [its own internal collections for test, which extend AtomicInteger](https://github.com/ReactiveX/RxJava/blob/2.x/src/main/java/io/reactivex/internal/util/VolatileSizeArrayList.java).

However, when asserting on that list, AssertJ will detect that list is of type AtomicInteger and print integer value instead of list contents on errors.

#### Example

Add to gradle:

```
compile "io.reactivex.rxjava2:rxjava:2.2.8"
compile "org.assertj:assertj-core:3.11.1"
```

Execute:
```java
Flowable<String> textObservable = Flowable.just("A", "B", "C");

List<String> receivedEntries = textObservable.test().values();

// Prints [A, B, C] normally
System.out.println(receivedEntries);

// Prints AtomicInteger(3) when assert fails
assertThat(receivedEntries).isEmpty();
```
